<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="iddc2db63b-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06" identifier="/us/usc/t12/s1742"><num value="1742">§ 1742.</num><heading> Rules and regulations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary is authorized and directed to make such rules and regulations as may be necessary to carry out the provisions of this subchapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="iddc2db63c-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06">(<ref href="/us/act/1934-06-27/ch847">June 27, 1934, ch. 847</ref>, title VI, § 607, as added <ref href="/us/act/1941-03-28/ch31/s1">Mar. 28, 1941, ch. 31, § 1</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/55/61">55 Stat. 61</ref>; amended <ref href="/us/act/1950-04-20/ch94">Apr. 20, 1950, ch. 94</ref>, title I, § 122, <ref href="/us/stat/64/59">64 Stat. 59</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/90/19/s1/a/3">Pub. L. 90–19, § 1(a)(3)</ref>, <date date="1967-05-25">May 25, 1967</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/81/17">81 Stat. 17</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
